{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"81fa5aff-d49c-447a-94fe-b266a55172a0","content":"The change is straightforward. In your project file, either **remove** the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property or set it to `false`:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove or set to false: -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` 3.8.0 already defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so removing that property is all you need.\n\n**Other things to watch for:**\n\n1. **CLI change** — Use `dotnet test` as before, but some older CLI flags (e.g., `--logger`) may behave differently. Use `dotnet test -- --help` to see the new options.\n2. **`.runsettings`** — Most settings still work, but verify yours; some VSTest-specific nodes are ignored.\n3. **Custom adapters/loggers** — If you reference VSTest-specific adapters (e.g., `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` or custom `ITestLogger` implementations), you'll need their Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n4. **CI integration** — If your CI relies on TRX output, add `--results-directory` and the appropriate result reporter extension.\n\nStart by dropping the property, run `dotnet test`, and fix anything that surfaces.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e1fbd763-d0d4-4d71-833a-79a43cb7f041","outputTokens":338,"requestId":"0830:1DCDBF:7D37527:8B75B31:69EABEC0"},"id":"d2beeafc-59fb-4409-a020-d0227e0491da","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:52:26.107Z","parentId":"ef972425-b009-4ca0-9a85-b2b9e12b527b"}
